  "sourceNotes": "Two-layer traybake bars with a shortbread or pastry base and a sweetened coconut or nut topping are documented in North American and British home-baking literature from the early twentieth century. Fannie Farmer, The Boston Cooking-School Cook Book (first edition 1896, fully in the public domain and available at Project Gutenberg), describes similar layered bar formats. The golden syrup coconut topping style is found in British and Canadian domestic baking guides from the 1920s.",
